### (1) Translation of the Story into English:

The King of Wei was plotting schemes during the court session, and none of his ministers could catch him. After the court session, he returned with a look of satisfaction. Wu Qi (a famous statesman in ancient China) said, "Have you heard of the words of King Zhuang of Chu spoken by your ministers?" The King of Wei replied, "What were the words of King Zhuang of Chu?" Wu Qi responded, "When King Zhuang of Chu was plotting schemes during the court session, none of his ministers could catch him. After the court session, he returned with a look of concern. Lord Shen and Minister Wu went forward and asked, 'Why do we have a look of concern?' King Zhuang of Chu said, 'I am plotting schemes during the court session, and none of my ministers can catch me. This is why I feel concerned. The advice from the sage in the middle, which said, "Those who consider themselves teachers are kings, those who gain friends are emperors, those who are doubtful are preserved, and those who plot schemes without thinking about themselves will perish," is why I feel concerned. Now, with unqualified individuals like me plotting schemes and none of my ministers can catch me, is our country on the verge of collapse? This is why I feel concerned.'" King Zhuang of Chu felt concerned, while the King of Wei felt pleased. The King of Wei bowed again and said, "Heavenly Master, you have corrected our mistakes."

